    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>drained butter beans</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>to the pan with the mushrooms and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add your<strong> mayo</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong>, your<strong> chives</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 1 min further or until warmed through – these are your <strong>smoky cayenne mushrooms</strong></p>",
